**Clinical Reasoning:**
Pelvic ultrasound, particularly transvaginal ultrasound, is the earliest safe method to confirm pregnancy and assess viability by identifying fetal cardiac activity, which becomes visible around 6–8 weeks of gestation. While hCG levels (option C) can support diagnosis, they cannot definitively confirm live pregnancy independently, whereas ultrasound directly detects embryonic structures and cardiac motion.

